le.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20an%20issue%20I%20care%20deeply%20about.%20When%20I%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2019%2F06%2F21%2Fbusiness%2Fgoldman-transgender.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecame%20out%20in%202019%20at%20Goldman%20Sachs%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20I%20was%20wildly%20excited%2C%20but%20I%20was%20also%20petrified.%20I%20now%20know%20that%20my%20co-workers%20were%20fearful%2C%20too%20%E2%80%94%20fearful%20that%20they%20would%20say%20or%20do%20something%20that%20would%20offend%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20more%20I%20think%20about%20this%20question%2C%20the%20more%20convinced%20I%20am%20that%20the%20answer%20is%20simple.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMaking%20the%20workplace%20more%20accommodating%20for%20people%20who%20are%20transitioning%20isn't%20much%20different%20than%20what%20most%20people%20consider%20doing%20if%20they%20have%20a%20friend%2C%20family%20member%2C%20or%20colleague%20going%20through%20a%20difficult%20personal%20situation.%20Here%20are%20a%20few%20key%20things%20to%20remember%20to%20make%20the%20process%20easier%20for%20everyone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E1.%20Just%20be%20kind%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20days%2C%20kindness%20toward%20the%20transgender%20and%20broader%20LGBTQ%2B%20community%20has%20dried%20up.%20It's%20in%20short%20supply%20at%20the%20time%20we%20need%20it%20most%20%E2%80%94%20a%20time%20when%20large%20swaths%20of%20American%20society%20have%20turned%20their%20backs%20on%20us%2C%20and%20politicians%2C%20in%20a%20cynical%20ploy%20in%20the%20name%20of%20protecting%20children%2C%20want%20to%20drum%20us%20out%20of%20existence%2C%20or%20at%20least%20de-legitimize%20our%20experience.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20heart%20of%20it%2C%20transgender%20people%20are%20like%20all%20other%20human%20beings%3A%20We%20want%20the%20same%20common%20courtesy%20extended%20to%20others%20and%20to%20be%20allowed%20to%20spend%20our%20lives%20as%20the%20people%20we%20are%20meant%20to%20be.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E2.%20Accept%20us%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAcceptance%20is%20a%20basic%20form%20of%20kindness%2C%20and%20we%20would%20be%20very%20thankful%20for%20just%20that.%20Dare%20we%20hope%20that%20when%20we%20are%20struggling%20with%20our%20identities%20and%20going%20through%20sometimes%20lengthy%2C%20dramatic%2C%20and%20confusing%20transitions%2C%20we%20get%20something%20approaching%20empathy%20and%20generosity%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20a%20couple%20you%20knew%20had%20a%20child%20with%20a%20rare%20illness%20or%20a%20psychiatric%20disorder%2C%20what%20would%20you%20do%3F%20You'd%20probably%20ask%20if%20there%20was%20anything%20you%20could%20do%20to%20help.%20Maybe%20you'd%20do%20a%20little%20research%20and%20ask%20a%20medical%20expert%20you%20know%20about%20the%20condition.%20Armed%20with%20additional%20information%2C%20you%20might%20then%20ask%20more%20specifically%20and%20in%20a%20more%20educated%20way%20how%20you%20could%20help.%20Why%20not%20do%20something%20similar%20with%20friends%20or%20acquaintances%20who%20have%20transgender%20children%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E3.%20Recognize%20that%20this%20life%20isn't%20easy%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20been%20an%20active%20alcoholic%20and%20suffered%20from%20depression%20most%20of%20my%20life.%20I'm%20also%20a%20suicide%20survivor.%20I%20attribute%20much%20of%20these%20experiences%20to%20my%20%3Cem%3Egender%20dysphoria%20%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%94%C2%A0a%20person's%20unease%20when%20they%20feel%20that%20the%20sex%20they%20were%20assigned%20at%20birth%20does%20not%20match%20their%20gender%20identity%20%E2%80%94%20which%20was%20unrecognized%20by%20me%20and%20therefore%20untreated%20until%20very%20recently.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20of%20us%20know%20our%20entire%20lives%20that%20we%20are%20in%20the%20wrong%20gender%2C%20but%20some%20of%20us%20(like%20me)%20live%20in%20self-hatred%20and%20are%20not%20exactly%20sure%20why.%20I%20didn't%20consciously%20know%20I%20was%20transgender%20until%20I%20was%2057%2C%20but%20once%20I%20realized%20it%2C%20a%20life%20of%20detesting%20myself%20and%20the%20inability%20to%20look%20at%20myself%20in%20a%20mirror%20for%20four%20decades%20suddenly%20made%20total%20sense.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E4.%20It's%20the%20internal%20that%20counts%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoldman-sachs-pronouns-initiative-memo-2019-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETransgender%20transitions%3C%2Fa%3E%20partly%20involve%20altering%20one's%20outward%20appearance%20to%20look%20more%20masculine%20or%20feminine%20or%20a%20little%20of%20both%2C%20taking%20hormones%2C%20and%20surgically%20changing%20bodies.%20I've%20done%20all%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20one%20of%20the%20biggest%20misconceptions%20about%20transitions%20is%20that%20they%20are%20all%20%3Cem%3Eexternal%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20when%20the%20reality%20is%20that%20the%20%3Cem%3Einternal%20%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%94%20altering%20how%20we%20think%20about%20our%20identity%20and%20working%20with%20others%20to%20change%20how%20they%20perceive%20us%20%E2%80%94%20are%20by%20far%20much%20more%20consequential.%20The%20most%20rewarding%20experiences%20I've%20had%20since%20transitioning%20are%20those%20in%20which%20I%20was%20being%20completely%20accepted%20by%20a%20group%20of%20women%2C%20whether%20in%20a%20formal%20setting%20such%20as%20being%20recognized%20for%20my%20advocacy%20by%20the%20Girl%20Scouts%20of%20Greater%20New%20York%2C%20or%20just%20bumming%20around%20with%20girlfriends.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20the%20way%2C%20doesn't%20everybody%20%E2%80%94%20transgender%20and%20cisgender%20(non-transgender%20people)%20alike%20%E2%80%94%20spend%20much%20of%20their%20lives%20trying%20to%20understand%20what%20it%20means%20to%20be%20a%20man%2C%20woman%20or%20some%20combination%20of%20the%20two%3F%20It's%20called%20self-reflection%20and%20it's%20a%20universal%20human%20experience.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E5.%20Don't%20pretend%20it%20didn't%20happen%2C%20and%20don't%20be%20afraid%20to%20ask%20questions%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgay-goldman-sachs-partner-came-out-on-wall-street-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EI%20came%20out%20at%20Goldman%20Sachs%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202019%2C%20we%20did%20a%20flip-the-switch%20type%20of%20transition%3A%20I%20left%20work%20one%20day%20in%20the%20gender%20I%20was%20assigned%20at%20birth%20and%20the%20next%20business%20day%20I%20came%20to%20work%20in%20the%20gender%20I%20was%20meant%20to%20be.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20made%20sense%20for%20me%20because%20I%20had%20already%20been%20at%20the%20company%20for%2015%20years%20and%20knew%20many%20of%20my%20colleagues%20well%2C%20including%20all%20the%20senior%20executives.%20Goldman's%20HR%20team%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0known%20as%20Human%20Capital%20Management%20%E2%80%94%20partnered%20with%20me%20to%20help%20inform%20the%20people%20I%20worked%20with%20about%20what%20was%20happening.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20some%20of%20my%20colleagues%20were%20uncomfortable.%20I%20think%20part%20of%20the%20reason%20people%20experience%20anxiety%20is%20the%20concern%20that%20%26quot%3Bthe%20woke%20mob%26quot%3B%20will%20jump%20all%20over%20them%20if%20they%20make%20a%20mistake.%20If%20that's%20the%20case%2C%20some%20of%20us%20in%20the%20woke%20mob%20deserve%20blame.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20a%20work%20colleague%20came%20back%20from%20family%20leave%20after%20having%20had%20a%20baby%20or%20caring%20for%20a%20loved%20one%2C%20what%20would%20you%20do%3F%20You%20might%20ask%20something%20like%2C%20%26quot%3BWhat%20can%20I%20do%20to%20make%20you%20comfortable%20and%20ease%20your%20way%20back%20to%20the%20workplace%3F%26quot%3B%20As%20the%20person%20responds%20and%20you%20receive%20more%20information%2C%20you%20get%20more%20comfortable%2C%20and%20perhaps%20ask%2C%20%26quot%3BWhy%20don't%20you%20tell%20me%20more%20about%20your%20experience%2C%20if%20you're%20comfortable%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20a%20transgender%20person%20you%20know%20is%20physically%20transitioning%20in%20a%20noticeable%20way%20and%20you%20want%20to%20be%20supportive%20and%20encouraging%2C%20try%20saying%20something%20like%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20noticed%20some%20changes%2C%20and%20if%20you%20ever%20want%20to%20talk%20about%20it%2C%20I'm%20here.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhether%20it%20be%20internal%20or%20external%2C%20isn't%20every%20human%20being%20in%20transition%20their%20whole%20life%2C%20as%20their%20perception%20of%20who%20they%20are%20changes%20and%20evolves%3F%20It's%20important%20to%20remember%20we're%20very%20much%20in%20the%20realm%20of%20normal%20human%20experience%2C%20and%20we%20all%20deserve%20the%20same%20kindness%2C%20courtesy%20and%20consideration%20that%20every%20human%20being%20merits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EMaeve%20DuVally%20is%20a%20former%20Goldman%20Sachs%20executive%20and%20author%20of%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3Fh%3Dedac8eb357a794fa9c3f5be7000b77fce8307146ec713cae189d560ed8e5200f%26postID%3D64d3df5a29ea7163e0e07c1a%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Faffiliate.insider.com%252F%253FamazonTrackingID%253Dbiauto-61384-20%2526h%253Dbf76a54b47d1f9d67b0ef3edc26f8eed8d5cc45ab7a25c63d6b43cf59ad6772f%2526postID%253D64d676d0837033154c8a9f89%2526site%253Dbi%2526u%253Dhttps%25253A%25252F%25252Fwww.amazon.com%25252FMaeve-Rising-Coming-Corporate-America%25252Fdp%25252F1736795414%25252Fref%25253Dsr_1_1%25253Fkeywords%25253Dmaeve%25252Bduvally%252526qid%25253D1691777300%252526s%25253Dbooks%252526sprefix%25253Dmaeve%25252Bdu%2525252Cstripbooks%2525252C121%252526sr%25253D1-1%2526platform%253Dbrowser%2526sc%253Dfalse%2526disabled%253Dfalse%2526tag%253Dbisafetynet2-20%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3E%26quot%3BMaeve%20Rising%3A%20Coming%