%20Sun%20is%20the%20nearest%20star%20and%20the%20largest%20object%20in%20the%20solar%20system.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EISRO%20estimates%20the%20age%20of%20the%20Sun%20to%20be%204.5%20billion%20years.%20It%20is%20a%20hot%20glowing%20ball%20of%20hydrogen%20and%20helium%20gases.%20The%20distance%20to%20the%20sun%20from%20the%20earth%20is%20about%20150%20million%20kilometers%2C%20and%20is%20the%20source%20of%20energy%20for%20our%20solar%20system.%20Without%20the%20solar%20energy%20the%20life%20on%20earth%2C%20as%20we%20know%2C%20cannot%20exist.%20The%20gravity%20of%20the%20sun%20holds%20all%20the%20objects%20of%20the%20solar%20system%20together.%20At%20the%20central%20region%20of%20the%20sun%2C%20known%20as%20'core'%2C%20the%20temperature%20can%20reach%20as%20high%20as%2015%20million%20degree%20Celsius.%20At%20this%20temperature%2C%20a%20process%20called%20nuclear%20fusion%20takes%20place%20in%20the%20core%20which%20powers%20the%20sun.%20The%20visible%20surface%20of%20the%20sun%20known%20as%20photosphere%20is%20relatively%20cool%20and%20has%20temperature%20of%20about%205%2C500%20degrees%20Celsius.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%221iqbo6lg%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-08%2F1iqbo6lg_isro_625x300_14_August_23.jpg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia's%20Chandrayaan-3%20is%20racing%20for%20its%20rendezvous%20with%20the%20South%20Pole%20of%20the%20moon%20on%20August%2023%2C%202023.%20Within%20weeks%20of%20that%2C%20the%20Indian%20space%20agency%20seeks%20to%20launch%20its%20nearly%201500%20kilogram%20scientific%20robotic%20satellite%20to%20keep%20a%20continuous%20eye%20on%20the%20Sun.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20will%20be%20India's%20first%20dedicated%20mission%20to%20monitor%20the%20Sun%2C%20especially%20to%20understand%20what%20happens%20when%20the%20Sun%20gets%20angry.%20A%20solar%20observatory%20made%20at%20a%20cost%20of%20Rs%20400%20crores.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIndia's%20Aditya%20L1%20satellite%20is%20a%20space%20based%20protector%20of%20sorts%2C%20keeping%20an%20eye%20on%20solar%20flares%20and%20ensuing%20solar%20storms'%20explained%20S%20Somanath%2C%20Chairman%2C%20ISRO%2C%20adding%20that%20%26quot%3BAditya%20L1%26quot%3B%20will%20look%20at%20Sun%20continuously%20hence%20it%20can%20thus%20forewarn%20us%20of%20imminent%20solar%20electro-magnetic%20effects%20on%20Earth%20and%20thus%20protect%20our%20satellites%2C%20and%20other%20power%20electrical%20and%20communications%20networks%20from%20getting%20disrupted%20and%20help%20continuing%20normal%20operations%20by%20operating%20them%20in%20'safe%20modes%2C%20till%20the%20solar%20storm%20passes%20by'%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAll%20life%20on%20earth%20is%20dependent%20on%20the%20Sun%2C%20both%20for%20solar%20radiation%20that%20helps%20plants%20capture%20the%20carbon%20and%20glucose%20through%20photosynthesis%2C%20the%20Earth%20really%20falls%20within%20the%20so%20called%20'Goldilocks%20Zone'%20neither%20too%20near%20the%20Sun%20nor%20too%20far%20just%20the%20right%20distance%20so%20that%20life%20could%20evolve%20on%20the%20planet.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%20%26quot%3BIndia%20has%20assets%20worth%20over%20Rs%2050%2C000%20crores%20in%20space%20with%20over%20fifty%20operational%20satellites%20and%20they%20need%20to%20be%20protected%20against%20the%20anger%20of%20the%20Sun'%20explains%20Mr%20Somanath.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20a%20large%20solar%20flare%20comes%20out%20of%20the%20Sun%20it%20can%20literally%20fry%20the%20electronics%20of%20the%20satellites.%20To%20protect%20them%2C%20space%20engineers%20shutdown%20the%20electronics%20and%20keen%20them%20in%20safe%20shut%20down%20state%20till%20highly%20charged%20storm%20passes%20over.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20spacecraft%20shall%20be%20placed%20in%20a%20halo%20orbit%20around%20the%20Lagrange%20point%201%20(L1)%20of%20the%20Sun-Earth%20system%2C%20which%20is%20about%201.5%20million%20km%20from%20the%20Earth.%20A%20satellite%20placed%20in%20the%20halo%20orbit%20around%20the%20L1%20point%20has%20the%20major%20advantage%20of%20continuously%20viewing%20the%20Sun%20without%20any%20occultation%2Feclipses.%20This%20will%20provide%20a%20greater%20advantage%20of%20observing%20the%20solar%20activities%20and%20its%20effect%20on%20space%20weather%20in%20real%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20spacecraft%20carries%20seven%20payloads%20to%20observe%20the%20photosphere%2C%20chromosphere%20and%20the%20outermost%20layers%20of%20the%20Sun%20(the%20corona)%20using%20electromagnetic%20and%20particle%20and%20magnetic%20field%20detectors.%20Using%20the%20special%20vantage%20point%20L1%2C%20four%20payloads%20directly%20view%20the%20Sun%20and%20the%20remaining%20three%20payloads%20carry%20out%20in-situ%20studies%20of%20particles%20and%20fields%20at%20the%20Lagrange%20point%20L1%2C%20thus%20providing%20important%20scientific%20studies%20of%20the%20effect%20of%20solar%20dynamics%20in%20the%20interplanetary%20medium.%20The%20scientific%20instruments%20of%20Aditya%20L1%20are%20expected%20to%20provide%20most%20crucial%20information%20to%20understand%20the%20problem%20of%20coronal%20heating%2C%20coronal%20mass%20ejection%2C%20pre-flare%20and%20flare%20activities%20and%20their%20characteristics%2C%20dynamics%20of%20space%20weather%2C%20propagation%20of%20particle%20and%20fields%20etc.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Indian%20space%20agency%20in%20its%20statement%20said%20the%20major%20science%20objectives%20of%20Aditya-L1%20mission%20are%3A%20The%20study%20of%20solar%20upper%20atmospheric%20(chromosphere%20and%20corona)%20dynamics.%20Study%20of%20chromospheric%20and%20coronal%20heating%2C%20physics%20of%20the%20partially%20ionized%20plasma%2C%20initiation%20of%20the%20coronal%20mass%20ejections%2C%20and%20flares.%20Observe%20the%20in-situ%20particle%20and%20plasma%20environment%20providing%20data%20for%20the%20study%20of%20particle%20dynamics%20from%20the%20Sun.%20Physics%20of%20solar%20corona%20and%20its%20heating%20mechanism.%20Diagnostics%20of%20the%20coronal%20and%20coronal%20loops%20plasma%3A%20Temperature%2C%20velocity%20and%20density.%20Development%2C%20dynamics%20and%20origin%20of%20CMEs.%20Identify%20the%20sequence%20of%20processes%20that%20occur%20at%20multiple%20layers%20(chromosphere%2C%20base%20and%20extended%20corona)%20which%20eventually%20leads%20to%20solar%20eruptive%20events.%20Magnetic%20field%20topology%20and%20magnetic%20field%20measurements%20in%20the%20solar%20corona.%20Drivers%20for%20space%20weather%20the%20origin%2C%20composition%20and%20dynamics%20of%20solar%20wind.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EISRO%20said%20the%20Aditya-L1%20mission%2C%20will%20study%20the%20photons%20and%20the%20solar%20wind%20ions%20and%20electrons%20emitted%20by%20the%20Sun%2C%20and%20the%20associated%20interplanetary%20magnetic%20field%2C%20from%20a%20halo%20orbit%20around%20the%20first%20Sun-Earth%20Lagrange%20point%20(L1).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20way%2C%20even%20as%20ISRO%20attempts%20to%20soft%20landing%20on%20the%20moon%2C%20it%20is%20getting%20ready%20to%20do%20a%20celestial%20'surya%20namaskar'%20through%20the%20Aditya%20satellite.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E(Pallava%20Bagla%20is%20co-author%20of%20the%20books%20'Destination%20Moon'%2C%20and%20'Reaching%20for%20the%20Stars%3A%20India's%20Journey%20to%20Mars%20and%20Beyond'.%20He%20can%20be%20reached%20on%20pallava.bagla%40gmail.com)%20%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692002820000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-08%2Fqgjo94po_isro_625x300_14_August_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Faditya-l1-isro-sun-mission-with-moon-in-sight-isro-now-aims-for-the-sun-4296284%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22With%20the%20moon%20well%20within%20its%20sight%2C%20the%20Indian%20Space%20Research%20Organization%20(ISRO)%20is%20now%20aiming%20for%20the%20Sun.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Faditya-l1-isro-sun-mission-with-moon-in-sight-