the%20scholar%E2%80%99s%20findings.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20August%201%2C%20matters%20heated%20up%20when%20Ashoka%20University%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FAshokaUniv%2Fstatus%2F1686353237904150528%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%257Ctwcamp%255Etweetembed%257Ctwterm%255E1686353237904150528%257Ctwgr%255Ea444ea8270339f33c2b901b832abe4cceb3b2398%257Ctwcon%255Es1_%26ref_url%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Fscroll.in%2Farticle%2F1053658%2Fashoka-university-criticised-for-dissociating-itself-from-professors-paper-on-election-manipulation%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%20issued%20a%20statement%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3Edistancing%20itself%20from%20Das%E2%80%99s%20paper%2C%20saying%20it%20was%20dismayed%20by%20the%20speculation%20and%20debate%20it%20had%20generated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20contacted%20him%20on%20Sunday%20evening%20to%20see%20if%20he%20would%20be%20in%20a%20position%20to%20talk%2C%20Das%20messaged%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%20am%20not%20engaging%20with%20media%20at%20this%20point.%20I%20am%20focused%20on%20getting%20my%20paper%20published%20before%20contemplating%20media%20engagement.%E2%80%9D%20When%20questioned%20explicitly%20about%20whether%20he%20had%20quit%20his%20position%2C%20Das%20did%20not%20reply.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAsked%20by%20%3Ci%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fi%3E%20if%20Das%20had%20resigned%20of%20his%20own%20accord%2C%20a%20faculty%20member%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CYou%20know%20how%20this%20is%20always%20a%20grey%20area.%20One%20is%20pushed%20to%20a%20point%20where%20the%20only%20way%20one%20can%20save%20one%E2%80%99s%20dignity%20is%20by%20resigning.%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%9CWe%20know%20that%20a%20lot%20went%20on%20behind%20closed%20doors%E2%80%9D%20before%20Das%20put%20in%20his%20papers%2C%20a%20second%20Ashoka%20academic%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20a%20third%20faculty%20member%20familiar%20with%20the%20development%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%E2%80%99ve%20been%20trying%20as%20hard%20as%20possible%20to%20get%20him%20to%20stay%E2%80%A6.%20He%20has